OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A portrait of Welsh slave owner Sir    
OL,6, Thomas Picton has been taken down from 
OL,7, National Museum Cardiff.               
OL,9,FIt had been on almost continuous       
OL,10,Fdisplay for more than 100 years.       
OL,12,FIt has been described as "the beginning
OL,13,Fof a journey" by National Museum Wales.
OL,14,FIts chief executive Fadhili Maghiya    
OL,15,Fsaid the move had "huge significance". 
OL,17,FThe museum worked with young people    
OL,18,Ffrom African communities to re-imagine 
OL,19,Fhow the Picton portrait should be      
OL,20,Fdisplayed and interpreted in future.   
